===In humans===
In human, circulating CD34+ hematopoietic stem cells ([[HSC]]) reside in bone marrow. They produce precursors of T lymphocytes, which seed the [[thymus]] (thus becoming thymocytes) and differentiate under influence of the [[Notch protein|Notch]] and its ligands.

Early, double negative thymocytes express (and can be identified by) [[CD2]], [[CD5]] and [[CD7]]. Still during the double negative stage, [[CD34]] expression stops and [[CD1]] is expressed. Expression of both CD4 and CD8 makes them ''double positive'', and matures into either CD4+ or CD8+ cells.<ref name=Robbins12-13>Figure 12-13 in: {{cite book |author=Mitchell, Richard Sheppard; Kumar, Vinay; Abbas, Abul K.; Fausto, Nelson |title=Robbins Basic Pathology|publisher=Saunders |location=Philadelphia |year= |pages= |isbn=1-4160-2973-7 |doi=}} 8th edition.</ref>

